<item>
            <title>[AMQ-5551] The DiskBenchmark util doesn&apos;t sync (fsync) to disk for sync writes</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-5551</link>
                <project id="12311210" key="AMQ">ActiveMQ Classic</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We added a JVM flag, org.apache.activemq.file.skipMetadataUpdate, to control whether to force metadata syncs or not when sync&apos;ing to disk. Unfortunately, that flag was not applied to the section of code that does the sync writes. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Fix on the way.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
